  "prompt": "What are the best free WordPress plugins in 2014?",
  "response": "In 2014, several free WordPress plugins gained popularity and were considered among the best for enhancing website functionality, performance, and user experience. Here\u2019s a list of some of the top free WordPress plugins from that year:\n\n1. **Yoast SEO** - A widely used plugin for improving SEO on WordPress sites. It provides features like XML sitemaps, meta tags, and content analysis.\n\n2. **WooCommerce** - A powerful plugin that transforms a WordPress site into a fully functional eCommerce store.\n\n3. **Jetpack** - Developed by Automattic, it offers a suite of features including site stats, social sharing, security enhancements, and more.\n\n4. **Contact Form 7** - A flexible and user-friendly plugin for creating contact forms, allowing for easy customization.\n\n5. **Wordfence Security** - A robust security plugin that offers firewall protection and malware scanning to help secure WordPress sites.\n\n6. **W3 Total Cache** - A performance optimization plugin that improves site speed through caching mechanisms.\n\n7. **UpdraftPlus** - A backup plugin that allows users to easily back up their WordPress files and databases.\n\n8. **Akismet** - A spam filtering plugin that automatically detects and filters out spam comments on WordPress posts.\n\n9. **Instagram Feed** - A plugin that allows users to display their Instagram photos on their WordPress site, enhancing visual engagement.\n\n10. **Visual Composer** - A page builder plugin that enables users to create responsive layouts without needing to code.\n\n11. **NextGEN Gallery** - A powerful gallery management system designed for photographers and visual artists to showcase their work beautifully.\n\n12. **Simple Lightbox** - A lightweight and easy-to-use plugin that adds a lightbox effect to images.\n\nThese plugins were widely utilized and praised for their features and ease of use, making them essential tools for WordPress users in 2014. Keep in mind that the WordPress ecosystem is constantly evolving, and newer versions of these plugins may have been released since then.",
